<dl id="n12228p"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12228p">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12228p"> 228(p)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Big Seat</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">He answered neither yea nor nay until the first Communion Sabbath, when he seized the bread and wine from Old Shemmi and walked to <mark>the Big Seat</mark> <font color="green">[pulpit]</font>. He stood under the pulpit, the fringe of the minister&apos;s Bible-marker curling on the bald patch on his head. <small> Caradoc Evans, <a name="EVAN" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EVAN"><cite title="source">My People</cite></a> (1915) 11 [A Father in Sion]</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12219g" href="c12all.htm#c12219g">VI.C.12:219(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
